    "title": "Add-on sync AMO downloads should not skew metrics", 
    "comments": [
        {
            "date": "2011-12-06 16:56:55", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "This is a follow-up to add-on sync to address the problem of downloads from AMO skewing download metrics.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "We don't want automatic add-on installs via Sync to increment the download count. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This likely involves changing the \"src=api\" query string parameter to \"src=sync\" or something similar.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Gregory Szorc [:gps]", 
            "email": "Gregory Szorc [:gps]"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2011-12-20 15:22:40", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This is targeted for Firefox 11 because we don't want this to go to the masses as stable and skew metrics. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I'm hoping to get this fixed while 11 is still in Aurora.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Gregory Szorc [:gps]", 
            "email": "Gregory Szorc [:gps]"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2011-12-20 15:50:11", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Daniel on the metrics team handles the processing here.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Wil Clouser [:clouserw]", 
            "email": "Wil Clouser [:clouserw]"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2011-12-20 17:51:25", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This is mainly needed for add-on installs; ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "updates are pulled from the mirrors and don't get counted in metrics at all.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "If possible, it would also be good to add a parameter to the post-install add-on metadata ping so it can be differentiated from the post-install ping of a real installation. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Thanks!\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Justin Scott [:fligtar]", 
            "email": "Justin Scott [:fligtar]"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2011-12-20 18:41:56", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "At the moment, the location of the XPI is found out via querying AMO's API, via AddonRepository (RepositoryAddon.sourceURI). ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "That URL has ?src=api in it... ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "doing a string replace on that will work and is easily contained within the sync code. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Although it does feel rather awkward, IMO.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Gregory mentioned maybe switching to using Addon.sourceURI - for addons that have been updated since they were installed, this will point to the location of the last update, which isn't tracked (see comment 3). ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "That kinda solves not counting those installs in normal metrics... ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "but it means we can never have metrics for how many addons are installed via sync (which we want want to do in the future). ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "For addons that haven't been updated, it will point to a URL that does count towards the download count, and that URL should have a src=whatever parameter.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Rewriting URLs is fine when it's a AMO URL, but what to do if it's not a AMO URL? ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "IIRC, we don't support syncing those addons now, but plan to in the future. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Rewriting those URLs could potentially break them.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "As for the post-install metadata ping... ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "that seems like it would be doable, but awkward - kinda feels like contaminating the AddonsManager API :\\ AMO is queried as soon as the XPI is downloaded and the install.rdf manifest can be read - ie, before the install starts. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Would need to add a flag to AddonManager.getInstallForURL(), and pass that all the way through to eventually where AddonRepoistory.cacheAddons() is called. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "If you do want to do that, having it generic and work like the AddonManager.UPDATE_WHEN_* constants would be nice.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Blair McBride (:Unfocused)", 
            "email": "Blair McBride (:Unfocused)"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2011-12-22 08:18:22", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "When the src param changes, just remember to add the new one to the valid list in the amo db table so we pick it up and export the id.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Daniel Einspanjer :dre [:deinspanjer]", 
