                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The metadata ping and install ping are pretty much the same, and the way we tell them apart for metrics purposes is that the metadata ping will have the default theme's GUID in it, while an install ping will only have the add-on that was just installed. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Explicitly differentiating them would be helpful, especially for other apps like mobile which doesn't have a default theme so we can't tell the difference at all.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "My main concern regarding install sources was with the API download URL, which should indicate it was downloaded via sync and not the user. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "A parameter on the metadata install lookup would be interesting but isn't necessary -- we don't currently use that ping for anything metrics-wise and simply filter them out of the daily metadata background checks.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
